Sep 14 2009 	Really good Midtown hotel	My wife &amp; I really enjoyed our stay here from 4-13 Sep. The location is great (2 blocks from Times Square/Theatre District &amp; the Port Authority Bus Terminal) &amp; we got an excellent rate, especially for Midtown. Subway &amp; bus stops are within 1 block.First, the bad news: there is no micro-fridge or on-site laundry. When we made reservations back in June, the Choice website had these amenities listed for this hotel. Unfortunately, they do not have them yet. We were really bummed at first since we were expecting these features. However, there are dozens of restaurants, delis, fast food joints, pizza, bars, &amp; cafes selling reasonably-priced food within a few minutes walk on both 8th &amp; 9th Ave. (Amy's Bread at 672 9th Ave has tasty baked goods &amp; The Big Apple Deli on 9th near 42nd St. has good prices on deli meat, plus an adjacent fruit &amp; veg. market). For laundry, there are 2 coin-op laundries on 9th Ave, near 46th St. &amp; 48th St. (machines are $2.25 each). The hotel staff said that they were unable to secure those items by opening date, but will be coming soon.Now the good news: customer service &amp; hospitality is absolutely excellent here. The staff is really friendly &amp; professional. Housekeeping did a good job maintaining room cleanliness. The free continental breakfast is very good: cereal (4-6 although sugary kids stuff), toast (2), bagels (2), fruit (2), yogurt (1-2), waffles, Danish (2-3), croissants, mini-muffins (2), juice (2), coffee &amp; tea (both reg. &amp; decaf). The staff did a good job keeping everything stocked. They plan to add hard boiled eggs &amp; other stuff soon. Coffee &amp; tea is available all day &amp; the rooms have coffee makers. The flat screen TV has 26 channels including HBO, etc. (If your TV has fewer channels, ask the front desk staff to check &amp; reprogram the TV). The beds have Serta mattresses' &amp; 4 pillows each. There is an armoire for clothing with lots of hangers &amp; 2 small drawers (more storage for clothing would be better if staying several days). They have energy efficient CFL bulbs in the lamps &amp; the a/c-heater worked well. 44th St. can be noisy during the night, so you may want a room in the back. There is a free computer w/printer in the lobby which is handy if you don't want to bring your laptop.Overall, our stay was really good. I would definitely recommend this hotel to anyone looking for a new, clean hotel with a great free breakfast &amp; excellent customer service in Midtown.	
